dismissalComment.html: length ball, Kieswetter hits on the up but it goes straight up, long-off comes scampering in from the boundary and takes a well-judged diving catch

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke lbw b Bresnan 61 (67b 6x4 1x6 104m) SR: 91.04

dismissalComment.html: got him this time! A similar delivery to earlier in the over but this is much straight and up goes the finger! Bang in front this is, he swings across it and caught plumb in front, game over now is it?

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner c Kieswetter b Anderson 56 (61b 6x4 1x6 94m) SR: 91.8

dismissalComment.html: edged and that's a fantastic snag behind the stumps! Anderson pitched it up, having pushed Warner back, enticed him to drive and a thick edge flew towards first slip (which was vacant), meaning Kieswetter had to launch himself horizontally to grasp the ball. Warner, the danger man, is gone ... Is that a game changer?

cry for caught behind as Watson looked to back-cut, given not out and England, who were convinced, refer this, there's a noise...and a mark on Hot Spot, this is going to be out and indeed up goes the finger. Watson stood still and tried to angle the ball away and got a thin nick through. England knew straight away, Aleem Dar perhaps couldn't hear the nick because of the wind but DRS again shows its worth

headshotImage.caption: David Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: David Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: bumper, Hussey gets in a tangle, the ball hits him on the helmet ... and drops on to the stumps! Strange dismissal, that, Hussey mistimed his pull completely, was hit on the shoudler, then the helmet, the ball finally plopping on to the wicket

headshotImage.caption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: down the pitch, straight up and caught by Kieswetter. McKay went for a leg side heave to a back of a length ball that he tried to step down the track to but it just went up and the keeper went to his left to take it with both hands easily

gone! It looked stone dead, missed a full ball that beat the inside edge, he refers it but this is just out and indeed Hawk Eye confirms as such, that was a ridiculous referral! Right in front on the back pad, if that ain't out, nowt is

batsmen.shot: off side drive on front foot

commentTextItems.html: another huge swing and a miss

commentPostTextItems.html: So England win by 15 runs and beat Australia at Lord's for the first time since 1997. Eoin Morgan's innings setting up a solid total that they have defended comfortably in the end...Still four games to come in this series starting on Sunday at The Oval, join us then for all the best live coverage but goodbye for now...

headshotImage.longCaption: Brett Lee player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: slapped into the off side the come back for two
length ball, a heave and a miss and England have all but won

commentPreTextItems.html: Three sixes and a one required...

commentTextItems.html: inside edge behind square on the leg side to a length ball
length ball drilled down the ground

commentPreTextItems.html: So Finn to bowl the last over of the game, with 21 to win, this would be something outrageous for Australia to pull this off...

commentTextItems.html: steps to leg, gets hit on the body, they charge a run, Finn can't hit the bowler's end stump so they take a run
Broad follows Lee's shuffle to leg and gets it through his legs

commentTextItems.html: outside off, slapped off an inside edge just wide of the bowler
off stump and blocked into cover
wide outside off and that's a wide

commentPostTextItems.html: Still just about alive the Aussies...an edged four would make it interesting...

commentTextItems.html: a heave towards the leg side goes straight through Steve Finn on the 45, they take three out to the long leg boundary, Finn does well to save second time around
slapped down the ground to long off

commentPreTextItems.html: 28 from 12 balls, still in touch Australia, needs some heaving though...Broad to bowl his last...

commentTextItems.html: back of a length, tucked to backward square leg and that should win the game with Douherty on strike
blocked on off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Watson c Kieswetter b Finn 12 (18b 1x4 0x6 24m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: cry for caught behind as Watson looked to back-cut, given not out and England, who were convinced, refer this, there's a noise...and a mark on Hot Spot, this is going to be out and indeed up goes the finger. Watson stood still and tried to angle the ball away and got a thin nick through. England knew straight away, Aleem Dar perhaps couldn't hear the nick because of the wind but DRS again shows its worth

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey b Anderson 29 (38b 3x4 0x6 59m) SR: 76.31

dismissalComment.html: that will make him feel better! Bailey chops into his stumps. Was too close to guide down to third man and takes a bottom edge into the wood work.

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner c Kieswetter b Anderson 56 (61b 6x4 1x6 94m) SR: 91.8

dismissalComment.html: edged and that's a fantastic snag behind the stumps! Anderson pitched it up, having pushed Warner back, enticed him to drive and a thick edge flew towards first slip (which was vacant), meaning Kieswetter had to launch himself horizontally to grasp the ball. Warner, the danger man, is gone ... Is that a game changer?
